This recipe serves as a good base for an interesting dessert. To elevate the interest, be sure to cut the heavy chocolate flavor with a touch fruit. I used orange liquor instead of chocolate. I also garnished with candied orange rind. The orange workedd well with the mocha. This is a fairly easy recipe, especially if you like making cheesecakes.

